general 2019-12-29 13:33:58 It'll include an engine, wings, a steady flying capability, control, and not much more.

general 2019-12-29 13:39:07 Have fun flying!
general 2019-12-29 13:39:49 The controls for this type of craft are really simple. Just use W to accelerate, S to decelerate and your mouse to maneuver.
general 2019-12-29 13:40:30 The reason our plane will fly steadily is that the **center of mass **and **center of lift** match up very well.
general 2019-12-29 13:40:45 no its plane crayz time

general 2019-12-29 13:43:04 Have fun flying!
general 2019-12-29 13:43:42 Alright, now let's learn to fly. Press the green button with the icon of a plane on it in the bottom left. A new interface will pop up:
general 2019-12-29 13:44:08 - The big black space on the left is actually a speed indicator. You'll see what I mean when you fly.
general 2019-12-29 13:44:22 The controls for this type of craft are really simple. Just use W to accelerate, S to decelerate and your mouse to maneuver.
general 2019-12-29 13:45:15 - The camera icon lets you switch camera. There are three cameras - 1st person, 3rd person locked and 3rd person free. _The hotkey for this button is C._
general 2019-12-29 13:45:34 - The 'Back' arrow returns you to Build Mode.
general 2019-12-29 13:52:22 Building just about anything for the first time is a task many people struggle with. For this tutorial, we'll assume you've never played before.
general 2019-12-29 13:52:38 Let's start with the interface. There are six buttons on it:
general 2019-12-29 13:52:47 1. Build Tool - This lets you place blocks.
general 2019-12-29 13:52:54 2. Delete Tool - This lets you delete blocks.
general 2019-12-29 13:53:05 3. Parameter Tool - For the parts that can be modified this tool allows you to edit the keybinds or parameters of a part.
general 2019-12-29 13:55:06 4. Translate Tool - This will let you move your entire craft in any direction.
general 2019-12-29 13:55:25 5. Paint Tool – Allows the use of coloring any Parts in the game using any HEX color code or the preset colors.
general 2019-12-29 13:55:39 6. Play Button - This will put you into flight mode.
general 2019-12-29 13:56:43 Building just about anything for the first time is a task many people struggle with.
general 2019-12-29 13:57:09 Start by navigating to the 'build' tool (hammer icon) and pressing on the 'Basic Building Blocks' (cube icon) button at the top of the interface that pops up. From the menu, select the 'Block' button - it doesn't matter which button you press, as they are both exactly the same.
general 2019-12-29 13:57:32 Have fun flying!
general 2019-12-29 13:59:07 Before I tell you how to fly, there are a few things you really need to know:
general 2019-12-29 13:59:31 - To save your plane, use the save button in the bottom left corner.
general 2019-12-29 13:59:46 - The reason our plane will fly steadily is that the center of mass and center of lift match up very well. These two variables are ABSOLUTELY ESSENTIAL in aircraft building, especially when you start to scale up.
general 2019-12-29 14:01:22 Now let's move on to the control surfaces. The more we have, the more maneuverable our plane is.
general 2019-12-29 14:01:38 Navigate to the section below the basic building blocks button, with the image of a wing on it, and then place some control surfaces like this.
general 2019-12-29 14:01:53 The grey part of the control surfaces must face backward - if they face forwards, your controls will be inverted!
general 2019-12-29 14:03:40 The large arrow painted on the ground will show you the direction to build in (not building in this direction can lead to problems, as we'll discuss later).
general 2019-12-29 14:05:19 Building just about anything for the first time is a task many people struggle with.

general 2020-04-08 11:28:20 **In order to submit a suggestion, you must first be** `ranked.`
Don't know how to get a rank? Run the command `?rhelp` in <#384027830192832513>!

After you have received the `ranked` role, you can now use the following command to submit your suggestion.
```&suggest <your suggestion>```
A few things to keep in mind:
• Be sure that your suggestion is **detailed.**
• The `&suggest` command is for submitting suggestions for the game only. If you have suggestions for the Discord server, please direct them to an admin.
• Abusing the command in anyway may result in the removal of your ability to submit suggestions.
• Please check <#681209786942881806> and the pinned messages in <#507673335816126509> first before submitting your suggestion as it may have already been suggested before.
• Whitelisting/teambuilding **WILL NOT** be added. See here for details: https://discordapp.com/channels/384021699466756103/533294912586645521/688265764121214987
